paragraphs.text:
%psql 
SELECT  model_hits.day, COUNT(models.uuid) as count from models
INNER JOIN model_hits on models.uuid = model_hits.uuid
GROUP BY model_hits.day
HAVING 
 model_hits.day IN (Select day FROM model_hits GROUP BY day ORDER BY day DESC)
ORDER BY model_hits.day DESC;

%psql
        SELECT cloud, COUNT(models.uuid) from models
        INNER JOIN model_hits
        WHERE models.uuid=model_hits.uuid and model_hits.day = (SELECT day from model_hits GROUP BY day ORDER BY day DESC LIMIT 1)
        GROUP BY cloud
        ORDER BY cloud;

%psql



 SELECT version, COUNT(models.uuid) from models
        INNER JOIN model_hits
        WHERE models.uuid=model_hits.uuid AND model_hits.day = (SELECT day from model_hits GROUP BY day ORDER BY day DESC LIMIT 1)
        GROUP BY version
        ORDER BY version DESC;

%psql
SELECT COUNT(model_hits.day) AS NEW_TODAY from models
INNER JOIN model_hits on models.uuid = model_hits.uuid
where 
 model_hits.uuid IN (Select uuid FROM model_hits GROUP BY day ORDER BY day DESC LIMIT 1 OFFSET 0) AND 
 model_hits.uuid NOT IN (Select uuid FROM model_hits GROUP BY day ORDER BY day DESC LIMIT 1 OFFSET 1);

%psql
           

SELECT running, count(uuid)
        FROM (
            SELECT model_hits.uuid, count(model_hits.day) as running
            FROM models, model_hits
            WHERE models.uuid = model_hits.uuid
            GROUP BY model_hits.uuid
            HAVING model_hits.day=(SELECT day from model_hits ORDER BY day DESC LIMIT 1)
        )
        GROUP BY running
        ORDER BY running DESC;
